title: Highlights from the Mechanical Curator
description: The Digital Research Team at the British Library has curated this set of highlights from more than one million public domain images from within our digitised collection of over 65,000 books from the 17th, 18th and 19th centuries. For more information visit our Digital Scholarship Blog. All images on our Flickr Commons account are free to use and remix. Visit our blog for more information on our 1 Million public domain Flickr Commons upload.

title: 'Images Online: a selection'
description:
This set covers a range of topics, and include images from the 13th century Topographia Hibernica, the signature of William Shakespeare from a Blackfriars mortgage-deed, sections from the Hindu epic The Ramayana, illustrations from The Legend of Sleepy Hollow, drawings of eighteenth century Hungarian and Saxon dress, Georgian caricatures by Thomas Rowlandson, and many more.

These digital images are freely available for unrestricted use and reuse, and are of an ideal quality for blogging, teaching, and creative work. And if you want a super high quality image for any reason, these can be purchased from British Library Images Online.

title: World War I: Indian Army by H.D. Girdwood
description: A series of photographs depicting the Indian Army in the First World War, held by the British Library as Photo(24) and digitised as part of the Europeana Collections 1914-1918 program. They were uploaded to Wikimedia Commons in May 2013.

title: World War I: The Canadian Experience
description: Copyright deposits from Canadian photographers, sent to Britain between 1895 and 1924, contain many depictions of Canadians’ experiences of the First World War. Either produced by photographers on home soil or individuals in Europe employed by Lord Beaverbrook’s ‘Canadian War Records Office’ the photographs provide a wide ranging account of the many Canadians involved in and impacted by the war.
